  "texts": [
    "This is likely due to the fact that this strategy always assign 0 points to the \"worst\" explanations.",
    "Similar results can be observed in Figures 3c and 3e for the CASAS Milan dataset.",
    "Among the two prompting strategies, the one that more accurately reflects the trend of the user surveys considered in the experiments is the \"Best Explanation Strategy\", although it does not reflect how users rated explanations in the survey.",
    "We argue that this is because LLMs are trained using natural language and they are known for struggling when reasoning with numbers [15].",
    "Finally, while the most advanced model we adopted (i.e., GPT-4) is the one leading to the most similar results compared to the ones in the user surveys, even cheaper models (i.e., GPT-3.5) show a trend in line with user surveys."
